  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What happens when you withdraw linkedin invitation?",
  "response": "When you withdraw a LinkedIn invitation, the following happens:\n\n1. **Invitation is Removed**: The invitation you sent to the other person is deleted from their LinkedIn notifications and inbox. They will no longer see it.\n\n2. **No Notification Sent**: The recipient is not notified that you withdrew the invitation. They will simply no longer have it in their pending invitations list.\n\n3. **Ability to Reconnect**: After withdrawing the invitation, you can send a new invitation to the same person in the future if you choose to. However, LinkedIn may flag it as \"Pending\" again or require you to add a note explaining why you're reconnecting, depending on the situation.\n\n4. **LinkedIn Etiquette**: Withdrawing an invitation is generally considered a neutral action and is not unusual. It\u2019s often done if you sent an invitation by mistake, reconsidered the connection, or realized the person may not recognize you.\n\n5. **No Impact on Your Profile**: Withdrawing an invitation does not affect your LinkedIn profile, connections, or account in any way.\n\nIf you\u2019re considering withdrawing an invitation, it\u2019s a simple and discreet process with no negative consequences.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
